In [ ]:
def chart_regression(pred,y,sort=True):
  t = pd.DataFrame({'pred' : pred, 'y' : y.flatten()})
  if sort:
    t.sort_values(by=['y'],inplace=True)
  a = plt.plot(t['pred'].tolist(),label='prediction')
  b = plt.plot(t['y'].tolist(),label='expected')
  plt.ylabel('output')
  plt.legend()
  plt.show()

Remove non-numeric data from numeric columns¶

In [ ]:
numeric_columns_fixed = joined_data.copy()

# Remove letters from columns and convert to numeric
numeric_columns_fixed['Runned_Miles'] = pd.to_numeric(numeric_columns_fixed['Runned_Miles'].str.replace(r'[^0-9]', '', regex=True), errors='coerce')
numeric_columns_fixed['Engin_size'] = pd.to_numeric(numeric_columns_fixed['Engin_size'].str.replace(r'[^0-9]', '', regex=True), errors='coerce')


print(numeric_columns_fixed['Price'])
numeric_columns_fixed['Price'] = numeric_columns_fixed['Price'].replace('[^\d.]', '', regex=True).replace(r'^\s*$', np.nan, regex=True).astype('float64')

print(numeric_columns_fixed['Price'])

med = numeric_columns_fixed['Price'].median()
numeric_columns_fixed['Price'] = numeric_columns_fixed['Price'].fillna(med)

prices = numeric_columns_fixed['Price']

upper = mean + 2 * stddev

for column in columns_to_normalize:

    normalized_data[column] = zscore(normalized_data[column])

Models¶

Dense Models¶

100-50-25-10 Adam Model¶

In [ ]:
checkpointer = ModelCheckpoint(filepath="./dnn/best_weights.hdf5", verbose=0, save_best_only=True) # save best model

for i in range(1):
    print(i)
    #
    visible1 = Input(shape=(x.shape[1],))
    x1 = Dense(100, activation='relu')(visible1)
    x1 = Dense(50, activation='relu')(x1)
    x1 = Dense(25, activation='relu')(x1)
    dense1 = Dense(10, activation='relu')(x1)

    output = Dense(1)(dense1)

    model = Model(inputs=[visible1], outputs=output)
    model.compile(loss='mean_squared_error', optimizer='adam')
    monitor = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', min_delta=1e-3, patience=10, verbose=2, mode='auto')
    model.fit([x_train], y_train, validation_data=([x_test], y_test), callbacks=[monitor,checkpointer], verbose=2, epochs=1000)

200-150-60-25-10 Adam Model¶

In [ ]:
checkpointer = ModelCheckpoint(filepath="./dnn/best_weights.hdf5", verbose=0, save_best_only=True) # save best model

for i in range(1):
    print(i)
    #
    visible1 = Input(shape=(x.shape[1],))
    x1 = Dense(200, activation='relu')(visible1)
    x1 = Dense(150, activation='relu')(x1)
    x1 = Dense(60, activation='relu')(x1)
    x1 = Dense(25, activation='relu')(x1)
    dense1 = Dense(10, activation='relu')(x1)

    output = Dense(1, activation='relu')(dense1)

    model = Model(inputs=[visible1], outputs=output)
    model.compile(loss='mean_squared_error', optimizer='adam')
    monitor = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', min_delta=1e-3, patience=10, verbose=2, mode='auto')
    model.fit([x_train], y_train, validation_data=([x_test], y_test), callbacks=[monitor,checkpointer], verbose=2, epochs=1000)

200-150-60-25-10 Adam Tanh 1st Layer Model¶

In [ ]:
checkpointer = ModelCheckpoint(filepath="./dnn/best_weights.hdf5", verbose=0, save_best_only=True) # save best model

for i in range(1):
    print(i)
    #
    visible1 = Input(shape=(x.shape[1],))
    x1 = Dense(200, activation='tanh')(visible1)
    x1 = Dense(150, activation='relu')(x1)
    x1 = Dense(60, activation='relu')(x1)
    x1 = Dense(25, activation='relu')(x1)
    dense1 = Dense(10, activation='relu')(x1)

    output = Dense(1, activation='relu')(dense1)

    model = Model(inputs=[visible1], outputs=output)
    model.compile(loss='mean_squared_error', optimizer='adam')
    monitor = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', min_delta=1e-3, patience=10, verbose=2, mode='auto')
    model.fit([x_train], y_train, validation_data=([x_test], y_test), callbacks=[monitor,checkpointer], verbose=2, epochs=1000)

CNN Model¶

CNN 1 VGG Block Model

In [ ]:
checkpointer = ModelCheckpoint(filepath="./dnn/best_weights.hdf5", verbose=0, save_best_only=True) # save best model

for i in range(1):
    print(i)

    #
    visible2 = Input(shape=(64, 64, 3))
    x2 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(visible2)
    x2 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x2)
    x2 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x2)
    x2 = Dropout(0.2)(x2)
    flat1 = Flatten()(x2)


    #
    visible3 = Input(shape=(64, 64, 3))
    x3 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(visible3)
    x3 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x3)
    x3 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x3)
    x3 = Dropout(0.2)(x3)
    flat2 = Flatten()(x3)

    #
    visible4 = Input(shape=(64, 64, 3))
    x4 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(visible4)
    x4 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x4)
    x4 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x4)
    x4 = Dropout(0.2)(x4)
    flat3 = Flatten()(x4)


    #
    visible5 = Input(shape=(64, 64, 3))
    x5 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(visible5)
    x5 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x5)
    x5 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x5)
    x5 = Dropout(0.2)(x5)
    flat4 = Flatten()(x5)

    merge = concatenate([flat1, flat2, flat3, flat4])

    hidden1 = Dense(128, activation='relu')(merge)
    output = Dense(1)(hidden1)

    model = Model(inputs=[visible2, visible3, visible4, visible5], outputs=output)
    model.compile(loss='mean_squared_error', optimizer='adam')
    monitor = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', min_delta=1e-3, patience=10, verbose=2, mode='auto')
    model.fit([front_train, right_train, rear_train, left_train], y_train, validation_data=([front_test, right_test, rear_test, left_test], y_test), callbacks=[monitor,checkpointer], verbose=2, epochs=1000)


print('Training finished...Loading the best model')
print()
model.load_weights('dnn/best_weights.hdf5') # load weights from best model
model.summary()

checkpointer = ModelCheckpoint(filepath="./dnn/best_weights.hdf5", verbose=0, save_best_only=True) # save best model

for i in range(1):
    print(i)

    #
    visible2 = Input(shape=(64, 64, 3))
    x2 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(visible2)
    x2 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x2)
    x2 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x2)
    x2 = Dropout(0.2)(x2)
    x2 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x2)
    x2 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x2)
    x2 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x2)
    x2 = Dropout(0.2)(x2)
    flat1 = Flatten()(x2)


    #
    visible3 = Input(shape=(64, 64, 3))
    x3 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(visible3)
    x3 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x3)
    x3 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x3)
    x3 = Dropout(0.2)(x3)
    x3 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x3)
    x3 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x3)
    x3 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x3)
    x3 = Dropout(0.2)(x3)
    flat2 = Flatten()(x3)

    #
    visible4 = Input(shape=(64, 64, 3))
    x4 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(visible4)
    x4 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x4)
    x4 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x4)
    x4 = Dropout(0.2)(x4)
    x4 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x4)
    x4 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x4)
    x4 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x4)
    x4 = Dropout(0.2)(x4)
    flat3 = Flatten()(x4)


    #
    visible5 = Input(shape=(64, 64, 3))
    x5 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(visible5)
    x5 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x5)
    x5 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x5)
    x5 = Dropout(0.2)(x5)
    x5 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x5)
    x5 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x5)
    x5 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x5)
    x5 = Dropout(0.2)(x5)
    flat4 = Flatten()(x5)

    merge = concatenate([flat1, flat2, flat3, flat4])

    hidden1 = Dense(128, activation='relu')(merge)
    output = Dense(1)(hidden1)

    model = Model(inputs=[visible2, visible3, visible4, visible5], outputs=output)
    model.compile(loss='mean_squared_error', optimizer='adam')
    monitor = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', min_delta=1e-3, patience=10, verbose=2, mode='auto')
    model.fit([front_train, right_train, rear_train, left_train], y_train, validation_data=([front_test, right_test, rear_test, left_test], y_test), callbacks=[monitor,checkpointer], verbose=2, epochs=1000)

checkpointer = ModelCheckpoint(filepath="./dnn/best_weights.hdf5", verbose=0, save_best_only=True) # save best model

for i in range(1):
    print(i)
    #
    visible1 = Input(shape=(x.shape[1],))
    x1 = Dense(100, activation='relu')(visible1)
    x1 = Dense(50, activation='relu')(x1)
    x1 = Dense(25, activation='relu')(x1)
    dense1 = Dense(10, activation='relu')(x1)

    #
    visible2 = Input(shape=(64, 64, 3))
    x2 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(visible2)
    x2 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x2)
    x2 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x2)
    x2 = Dropout(0.2)(x2)
    x2 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x2)
    x2 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x2)
    x2 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x2)
    x2 = Dropout(0.2)(x2)
    flat1 = Flatten()(x2)


    #
    visible3 = Input(shape=(64, 64, 3))
    x3 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(visible3)
    x3 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x3)
    x3 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x3)
    x3 = Dropout(0.2)(x3)
    x3 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x3)
    x3 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x3)
    x3 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x3)
    x3 = Dropout(0.2)(x3)
    flat2 = Flatten()(x3)

    #
    visible4 = Input(shape=(64, 64, 3))
    x4 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(visible4)
    x4 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x4)
    x4 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x4)
    x4 = Dropout(0.2)(x4)
    x4 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x4)
    x4 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x4)
    x4 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x4)
    x4 = Dropout(0.2)(x4)
    flat3 = Flatten()(x4)


    #
    visible5 = Input(shape=(64, 64, 3))
    x5 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(visible5)
    x5 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x5)
    x5 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x5)
    x5 = Dropout(0.2)(x5)
    x5 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x5)
    x5 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x5)
    x5 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x5)
    x5 = Dropout(0.2)(x5)
    flat4 = Flatten()(x5)

    merge = concatenate([dense1, flat1, flat2, flat3, flat4])

    hidden1 = Dense(128, activation='relu')(merge)
    output = Dense(1)(hidden1)

    model = Model(inputs=[visible1, visible2, visible3, visible4, visible5], outputs=output)
    model.compile(loss='mean_squared_error', optimizer='adam')
    monitor = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', min_delta=1e-3, patience=10, verbose=2, mode='auto')

checkpointer = ModelCheckpoint(filepath="./dnn/best_weights.hdf5", verbose=0, save_best_only=True) # save best model

for i in range(1):
    print(i)
    #
    visible1 = Input(shape=(x.shape[1],))
    x1 = Dense(200, activation='relu')(visible1)
    x1 = Dense(150, activation='relu')(x1)
    x1 = Dense(60, activation='relu')(x1)
    x1 = Dense(25, activation='relu')(x1)
    dense1 = Dense(10, activation='relu')(x1)

    #
    visible2 = Input(shape=(64, 64, 3))
    x2 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(visible2)
    x2 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x2)
    x2 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x2)
    x2 = Dropout(0.2)(x2)
    x2 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x2)
    x2 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x2)
    x2 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x2)
    x2 = Dropout(0.2)(x2)
    flat1 = Flatten()(x2)


    #
    visible3 = Input(shape=(64, 64, 3))
    x3 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(visible3)
    x3 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x3)
    x3 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x3)
    x3 = Dropout(0.2)(x3)
    x3 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x3)
    x3 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x3)
    x3 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x3)
    x3 = Dropout(0.2)(x3)
    flat2 = Flatten()(x3)

    #
    visible4 = Input(shape=(64, 64, 3))
    x4 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(visible4)
    x4 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x4)
    x4 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x4)
    x4 = Dropout(0.2)(x4)
    x4 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x4)
    x4 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x4)
    x4 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x4)
    x4 = Dropout(0.2)(x4)
    flat3 = Flatten()(x4)


    #
    visible5 = Input(shape=(64, 64, 3))
    x5 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(visible5)
    x5 = Conv2D(32, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x5)
    x5 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x5)
    x5 = Dropout(0.2)(x5)
    x5 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x5)
    x5 = Conv2D(64, kernel_size=(3, 3), activation='relu')(x5)
    x5 = MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2, 2))(x5)
    x5 = Dropout(0.2)(x5)
    flat4 = Flatten()(x5)

    merge = concatenate([dense1, flat1, flat2, flat3, flat4])

    hidden1 = Dense(128, activation='relu')(merge)
    output = Dense(1)(hidden1)

    model = Model(inputs=[visible1, visible2, visible3, visible4, visible5], outputs=output)
    model.compile(loss='mean_squared_error', optimizer='adam')
    monitor = EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', min_delta=1e-3, patience=10, verbose=2, mode='auto')
    model.fit([x_train, front_train, right_train, rear_train, left_train], y_train, validation_data=([x_test, front_test, right_test, rear_test, left_test], y_test), callbacks=[monitor,checkpointer], verbose=2, epochs=1000)
